# DATA PREPROCESSING PIPELINE

# ---- Step 1: Resize to 224x224 ----
# All images are resized to 224x224 during loading to ensure
# homogeneous input dimensions required by the ResNet architecture

# ---- Step 2: Grayscale OR RGB Based on Model Requirements ----
# RGB format is preserved (.convert('RGB')) to match ResNet's
# 3-channel input requirements. Chest X-rays are naturally grayscale
# but are loaded as RGB where all 3 channels carry identical values

# ---- Step 3: Normalize Pixel Values ----
# Pixel values are scaled from [0, 255] to [0, 1] by dividing by 255
# This stabilizes gradient updates and accelerates model convergence

# ---- Step 4: Encode Labels ----
# String labels (NORMAL / PNEUMONIA) are encoded to binary integers
# (0 = Normal, 1 = Pneumonia) for model compatibility

# ---- Step 5: Merge Validation Set into Training Set ----
# The validation set contains only 16 images and is statistically
# unreliable. It will be merged into the training set and cross-validation
# will be used instead for proper model evaluation during training

# ---- Step 6: Oversample via Augmentation ----
# Data augmentation (rotation, flipping, shifting, zoom) 
# to the minority class to balance distribution and prevent model bias
# Augmentation is applied only to training data 
